description:
I put down my sandok ladle for a bit to be part of the Philippine Book Festival 2024, and I had a blast! 

It was a pinch-me-moment to be part of a panel alongside the people I would look up and research to learn more about Filipino foodâ€”Claude Tayag, Ige Ramos, and Clang Garcia. And this time, the saying, â€œNever meet your heroes,â€ doesnâ€™t apply because IRL, theyâ€™re gracious and personable and said nothing but nice things on stage about Filipino vegan versions and traditionally plant-based dishes.

And thanks to my publisher, @anvilpublishing, I had another opportunity to hold a book signing and meet people interested in Filipino vegan cooking â€”from professional chefs to newbie home cooks, curious omnivores, to longtime fellow vegans. Learning about them and their stories gives me insight into how I can improve my work and my craft.

The fun didnâ€™t stop there. When @nbdbphilippines says itâ€™s not just a book fair, itâ€™s a book experience, theyre not kidding. I saw colorful installations, people in costumes, kids playing native Filipino instruments or coloring some books, even local celebrities promoting Philippine literature, and social media influencers part of #booktok that make reading not just fun but also hip, and very much cool. I had FOMO not knowing the books they were talking about!

I came home wanting to read more books even trying new genres and topics by our own Filipino writers and artists. Iâ€™m planning to etch some time, even designate a reading nook, so hopefully itâ€™ll bloom into a routine.

All this new burst of inspiration came thanks to @bookfestph. Maraming salamat po for creating such an engaging event that was feast for the senses. Mabuhay po kayo! And thank you Anvil Publishing for always thinking of me and incorporating me into your events. I truly appreciate it. See you at the next one!

#booktokers #filipinofood #vegantok
